Bounded types are used to restric the types that can be used as type argument





Bounded Types at method level

public static <T extends Comparable<T>> T calculate(T num1, T num2){


    if(num1.conpareto(num2)<0) return num1 else return num2;

}



// Generic to add two methods
public static <T extends Number> double add(T num1, T num2){
    double result = num1.doubleValue() + num2.doubleValue();
    return result;

}


Bounded Types at class level
class Person extends Comparable<Personb>{

    @Override 
    public int compareTo(Person o){
        return Integer.compare(age,o.age);
    }
}